# CyberFin Nexus — Full Implementation Plan

A hackathon-winning, privacy-first platform fusing cyber threat telemetry with financial transactions using GNNs (GAT), Federated Learning, and RL-based attacker adaptation. Includes an interactive Streamlit dashboard with explainable AI, blockchain-like audit trails, and cross-bank collaboration simulation.

## Proposed Changes

### Project Structure & Dependencies

#### [NEW] [requirements.txt](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/requirements.txt)
- All pip dependencies: `torch`, `torch-geometric`, `networkx`, `streamlit`, `plotly`, `pandas`, `numpy`, `scikit-learn`, `matplotlib`

---

### Data Generation Module

#### [NEW] [data_generator.py](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/data_generator.py)
- **Realistic synthetic data** for 4 banks, 200+ accounts, 50+ devices, 500+ transactions
- Generates cyber logs (phishing, malware, brute-force attacks with IPs, timestamps, severity)
- Generates financial transactions with amounts, timestamps, currencies
- Creates mule ring structures (coordinated clusters of 3-8 accounts)
- Labels: ground-truth mule vs. legitimate accounts
- Outputs DataFrames for downstream consumption

---

### Graph Construction Module

#### [NEW] [graph_builder.py](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/graph_builder.py)
- Fuses cyber logs + transactions into a **heterogeneous graph**
- Node types: accounts, devices, external endpoints
- Edge types: `account↔device` (cyber), `account→account` (transaction), `account→external` (withdrawal)
- Node features: cyber risk score, transaction volume, velocity, device entropy, behavioral features
- Converts to PyTorch Geometric `Data` object with proper `edge_index`, `x`, and `y` tensors

---

### GNN Model (GAT with Attention)

#### [NEW] [models/gat_model.py](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/models/gat_model.py)
- 3-layer GAT with multi-head attention (8 heads → 8 heads → 1 head)
- Dropout + batch normalization for regularization
- `explain()` method returning attention weights per edge (for explainability)
- Outputs per-node risk scores (sigmoid)

---

### Federated Learning Simulation

#### [NEW] [federated/fl_engine.py](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/federated/fl_engine.py)
- Partitions data by bank ID → creates local datasets
- Trains local GAT models independently per bank
- **FedAvg** aggregation: averages model weights across banks
- Differential Privacy: adds calibrated Gaussian noise (ε=1.0) to gradients
- Tracks per-round accuracy/AUC for convergence visualization

---

### RL-Based Attacker Adaptation

#### [NEW] [rl/adversarial_sim.py](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/rl/adversarial_sim.py)
- Simulates attacker evolution strategies:
  - **Velocity reduction**: Mules slow transactions to evade velocity checks
  - **Amount splitting**: Large amounts broken into sub-threshold transfers (structuring/smurfing)
  - **Device rotation**: Attackers switch devices to break fingerprint links
  - **Behavioral mimicry**: AI-generated normal patterns
- After each attack mutation, retrains GAT incrementally (online learning)
- Reports detection rate before/after adaptation

---

### Blockchain Traceability

#### [NEW] [blockchain/audit_trail.py](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/blockchain/audit_trail.py)
- Mock hash-chain: each transaction gets SHA-256 hash linking to previous
- Immutable audit log with timestamps, risk scores, model decisions
- Tamper detection: verify chain integrity
- Export audit trail as JSON for regulatory compliance

---

### Streamlit Dashboard

#### [NEW] [app.py](file:///e:/VS%20Code/cyber/app.py)
- **Main entry point** — multi-page Streamlit app with sidebar navigation
- 6 interactive tabs:

| Tab | Contents |
|-----|----------|
| **🏠 Overview** | Problem statement, architecture diagram, key metrics cards |
| **🕸️ Nexus Graph** | Interactive Plotly network graph with risk-colored nodes, hover tooltips, edge attention weights |
| **🏦 Federated Learning** | Per-bank training metrics, FL convergence chart, privacy budget (ε) slider |
| **⚔️ Attack Simulation** | "Simulate Attack" button → shows before/after detection, RL adaptation metrics |
| **🔗 Audit Trail** | Blockchain hash-chain viewer, tamper verification, transaction timeline |
| **🚨 Alerts & Explainability** | Top-N flagged accounts, GAT attention heatmap, confidence scores, human-override toggle |

---

